SIMPLE: recompense
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recompense
<hw>Rec"om*pense</hw> <pr>(r⟦ecr⟧k"⟦ocr⟧m*p⟦ecr⟧ns)</pr>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Recompensed</conjf>
<pr>(-p?nst)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Recompensing</conjf> <pr>(-p?n`s?ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧compenser</ets>, LL. <ets>recompensare</ets>, fr.L. pref.
<ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>compensare</ets> to compensate. See
<er>Compensate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To render an equivalent to,
for service, loss, etc.; to requite; to remunerate; to
compensate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He can not <qex>recompense</qex> me better.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To return an equivalent for; to give compensation
for; to atone for; to pay for.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God <qex>recompenseth</qex> the gift.</q> <rj><qau>Robynson
(More's Utopia).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>recompense</qex>⟦br⟧
My rash, but more unfortunate, misdeed.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To give in return; to pay back; to pay, as something
earned or deserved.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Recompense</qex> to no man evil for evil.</q> <rj><qau>Rom.
xii. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To repay; requite; compensate; reward;
remunerate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recompense</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Recompense
<hw>Rec"om*pense</hw> <pr>(r?k"?m*p?ns)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To
give recompense; to make amends or requital.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recompense</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Recompense
<hw>Rec"om*pense</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧compense</ets>.]</ety> <def>An equivalent returned for
anything done, suffered, or given; compensation; requital; suitable
return.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To me belongeth vengeance, and <qex>recompense</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Deut. xxii. 35.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And every transgression and disobedience received a just
<qex>recompense</qex> of reward.</q> <rj><qau>Heb. ii. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Repayment; compensation; remuneration; amends;
satisfaction; reward; requital.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recompensement</ent>⟦br⟧
